Experimental Verification of the NKTg Law Using NASA Mercury Data in 2025

Independent Researcher: Nguyễn Khánh Tùng
ORCID: 0009-0002-9877-4137

Abstract

This report presents the results of the experimental verification of the NKTg Law through the simulation of Mercury’s orbit in 2025, using reference data from NASA JPL Horizons and the MESSENGER spacecraft. The study evaluates the conservation behavior of the quantity NKTg₁ = x × p and integrates real measured mass variation data to assess the consistency and predictive capability of the NKTg framework.

